. We attach great importance to the protection of your privacy and are committed to processing your personal data in accordance with French law and the strictest privacy standards. Please read this Privacy Policy carefully before using our service. By using
Mozart AI,
you accept the practices described in this Privacy Policy.
1. Collection and Use of Personal Data
1.1. When you use Mozart AI, we may collect certain types of personal data about you, such as your name, email address, profile information, and conversation history. We collect this data for the purpose of providing you with a personalized experience and improving our services.
1.2. We may also collect technical data, such as information about your device, IP address, log files, and cookies, to facilitate your use of Mozart AI, and analyze usage trends.
2. Protection and Storage of Personal Data
2.1. We take appropriate security measures to protect your personal data against unauthorized access, loss, alteration, or disclosure. We use encryption methods and advanced security protocols to ensure the confidentiality of your data.
2.2. Your personal data will be retained for the duration necessary for the purposes mentioned in this Privacy Policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law.
3. Sharing of Personal Data
3.1. We may share your personal data with third parties in the following cases:
a) When necessary to provide our services and respond to your requests.
b) When required by law, a court order, or a request from a competent government authority.
c) With your prior consent.
4. Cookies and Similar Technologies
4.1. We use cookies and other similar technologies to enhance your user experience, analyze usage trends, and personalize our service. You can configure your browser to refuse cookies, but this may limit certain features of Mozart AI
.
5. Links to Third-Party Sites
5.1. Mozart AI may contain links to third-party websites. This Privacy Policy does not apply to those sites. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of those third-party sites before providing your personal data.
6. Modification of the Privacy Policy
6.1. We reserve the right to modify this Privacy Policy at any time. The modifications will take effect upon their publication on our website or Mozart AI. We encourage you to regularly review this Privacy Policy to stay informed of any updates.
7. Subscription Terms and End-User License Agreement (EULA)
7.1. Mozart AI may offer paid subscriptions or in-app purchases. The details of these offerings, including pricing, payment methods, subscription duration, and terms and conditions, will be clearly communicated to the User within the application and governed by the End-User License Agreement (EULA). By subscribing or making in-app purchases, you agree to be bound by the terms and conditions specified in the EULA.
8.User Responsibility for Uploaded Content
8.1. Users are solely responsible for the content they upload to Mozart AI. By uploading content, users acknowledge and agree that they own or have the necessary permissions to use and share such content. We are not liable for any claims or disputes arising from the content uploaded by users. Users agree to indemnify and hold harmless Mozart AI from any legal action, costs, or damages resulting from their uploaded content.
